<ul class="pb_card_kit_shadow_deep_deselected p_md">
  To use the breakpoints for your custom css import screen sizes into your scss file:
    <br/>
    <code> @import "tokens/screen_sizes"; </code>
    <br/>
    <br/>


    <br/>
    Breakpoints: <br/>
     <code> $breakpoints: ( <br/>
       &nbsp; xs: 575px, <br/>
       &nbsp; sm: 576px, <br/>
       &nbsp; md: 768px, <br/>
       &nbsp; lg: 992px, <br/>
       &nbsp; xl: 1200px <br/>
     ); </code> <br/>
    
    <br/>

    You can use these like this:<br/> 
    <code>map-get($breakpoints, "sm"); // will return 576px</code><br/>

    <br/>

    Or as a function:<br/> 
    <code>breakpoint("sm") // will return 576px</code><br/>

    <br/>

    You can also use the break_at media query helper to make your code easier to understand: <br/> 
    <code> @include break_at(1290px) { <br/>
      &nbsp; .some_class { <br/>
      &nbsp; &nbsp; padding: 0; <br/>
      &nbsp; } <br/>
      } </code><br/>
    
    <br/>

    Or using the break-point function: <br/> 
    <code> @include break_at( breakpoint("sm") ) { <br/>
      &nbsp; .some_class { <br/>
      &nbsp; &nbsp; padding: 0; <br/>
      &nbsp; } <br/>
      } </code><br/>
</ul>